    <h2>Plant-Based Candy vs Plant-Based Supplements</h2>

    <p>This guide covers plant-based candy — gummy bears, sour worms, chocolate, and fruit snacks designed for enjoyment. But the plant-based gummy world extends into an entire supplement category: gelatin-free gummy vitamins, sleep aids, beauty formulas, and sports nutrition. The same pectin and agar-agar technology that makes vegan candy possible also makes vegan gummy supplements possible.</p>

    <p>Looking for vegan gummy vitamins instead? See our <a href="/vegan-gummies/">best vegan gummies guide</a> for the complete breakdown of plant-based supplements — from <a href="/best-melatonin-gummies/">melatonin gummies</a> for sleep to <a href="/best-hair-growth-gummies/">hair growth gummies</a> for beauty to <a href="/best-creatine-gummies/">creatine gummies</a> for fitness.</p>

    <!-- VERDICT -->
    <div class="verdict">
      <h3>The Verdict: Best Plant-Based Gummy Candy in 2026</h3>
      <p>The plant-based candy market has reached mainstream maturity. <strong>SmartSweets</strong> leads in low-sugar innovation, <strong>YumEarth</strong> leads in organic value, <strong>Surf Sweets</strong> leads in ingredient purity, and <strong>Unreal</strong> leads in premium chocolate. For families, <strong>Annie's</strong> delivers the most trusted organic fruit snack at the lowest price. For sour candy fans, <strong>SmartSweets Sour Blast Buddies</strong> prove that 3g sugar and genuine sourness can coexist.</p>
      <p>The gap between plant-based and conventional candy has essentially closed on flavor and continues to narrow on texture. By 2027, we expect pectin formulations to achieve complete texture parity with gelatin for most consumers. The remaining differentiator will be price — and even there, YumEarth and Black Forest have proven that organic, plant-based candy can compete at conventional price points.</p>
    </div>

